Shows which encoder achieved the highest processing speed for this specific test configuration.

Conditions:
• Only appears when 2 or more encoders are tested;
• Same input file and parameters for all encoders;
• Based on the fastest average processing speed;
• Calculated after 'Analyze Log' processing;

Not all encoder builds yield the same performance even with:
• Same source file;
• Identical parameters;
• Same encoder version.

This helps identify:
• Different compiler optimizations;
• CPU-specific instruction sets (SSE, AVX, AVX2);
• Memory access pattern variations;
• Multithreading implementation differences;
• Build configuration performance impact.

This allows direct performance comparison between different encoders under identical conditions.

